com.srchulo.roundrobin

Interface RoundRobinKeyValueIterator<K,V>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    java.util.Iterator<V>

    public interface RoundRobinKeyValueIterator<K,V>
extends java.util.Iterator<V>
    An Iterator that returns values associated with keys in Round-Robin order. Items can be added and removed in O(1) constant time. This Iterator will loop continuously.

      • add

        void add(K key,
         V value)
        Adds this key-value pair to the iterator. The key-value pair will be placed after the last value retrieved from Iterator.next(), and thus will be returned the next time Iterator.next() is called. This operation is performed in O(1) constant time. If no values have been added, this value is first.

      • remove

        void remove(K key)
        Removes the value associated with key from the Iterator. This operation is performed in O(1) constant time. It is safe to call this method while iterating. If this value would have been returned by Iterator.next() on the next call, the value after it will now be returned.
